<h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">RULES AND GUIDANCE</span></strong></h1>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Introduction</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>The Tennis Widows League was set up around 22 yrs ago by a group of friends who wanted to enjoy a friendly game of competitive tennis.  As the TWL has grown in numbers the Committee strive to promote the original intention of a “friendly competitive game” and for that reason we have introduced a Fair Game Policy.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Rules</span></strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Please take time to refresh your memory with the rules, as there have been some <strong>important</strong> additions.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Please make sure you check the scheduled matches and highlight them to alert you of any you may need to change re holidays etc.</p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Fixtures</span></strong></p>
<p>The enclosed fixture list informs you of your matches; dates, times and venues.  The league starts on Wednesday 17th April 2012 and your last match must be played by <strong>31st August 2012</strong>.  <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"> Any match played after this date is void</span></strong> as we need to get trophies engraved for our end of season do!</p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Half-Way Results</span></strong></p>
<p>By mid June all players should have played 8 matches. Please make sure that you have sent the results of <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">eight</span></strong> matches to your division representative by <strong>30th June 2012</strong>. If we do not receive 8 results by this date we will <strong>deduct 5 points</strong> from each couple not doing so.</p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">MATCHES</span></h1>
<p> </p>
<p>We recommend that the start time should be 6.30pm for the first 4 weeks and 7pm thereafter,<strong> do not assume this please contact your opponents.</strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Tennis Balls</span></strong></p>
<p>All ladies must provide <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">NEW TENNIS BALLS</span></strong> for their matches please; this will promote a more enjoyable game of tennis.  Do not assume your opponents should provide the balls make sure you have a set between you and your partner.</p>
<p>In the Premier Division home players must provide the <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">NEW</span></strong> tennis balls. Players listed on the left are deemed to be the home players.</p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Points System</span></strong></p>
<p>In each match 3 sets are played. The set ends when a couple reaches 6 games.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>One point</strong> is gained per game <strong>won</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>Two extra</strong> points are gained for each <strong>SET</strong> won.</p>
<p>Therefore it is possible to gain 24 points in a match.</p>
<p>NB if the points are equal at the end of the match the couple that who has won <strong>TWO</strong> sets wins the match.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Results</strong></p>
<p>The winning couple must send their match results in on the score card provided to their divisional representative within three days of the match been played.  Please agree the score with your opponents and <strong>both</strong> sign and date the card.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>TIP –</strong> Put the score cards in your bag so you’ve got them!</p>
