<h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">CANCELLATION OF COURTS</span></h1>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Please notify court owners as soon as possible if you do not need the court on the arranged date</span></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>•<span style="white-space: pre;"> </span>It is the responsibility of the cancelling couple to notify the court owner when they do not require the court.</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>•<span style="white-space: pre;"> </span>Please remember to cancel your courts where necessary.</strong></p>
<p> </p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">ABANDONED MATCHES</span></h1>
<p>A match which is abandoned for whatever reason must be recorded and replayed in the following way:-</p>
<p>•<span style="white-space: pre;"> </span>Call your division representative immediately and explain why the match has been abandoned.</p>
<p>•<span style="white-space: pre;"> </span>The <strong>current</strong> score, including the <strong>part played</strong> set score, must be recorded on a score card and sent to your div rep it must be <strong>dated</strong> and <strong>signed</strong> by all players.  Please make sure you record who was serving at the time of abandoning.</p>
<p>•<span style="white-space: pre;"> </span>At this point the total score of <strong>COMPLETED SETS</strong> and <strong>COMPLETED GAMES</strong> will be counted.</p>
<p>•<span style="white-space: pre;"> </span>You must resume the match from the <strong>Completed Game</strong> score you finished at and <strong>not</strong>, for example 15 - 30 of the abandoned game.</p>
<p>•<span style="white-space: pre;"> </span> Please record the resumed match score on a score card, date and sign and return it to your div rep.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Mobile Phones</span></strong></p>
<p>On no occasion should a match be postponed by means of text message or e-mail.  You must always speak to one of your opponents if you are not able to play on the scheduled date.</p>
<p><strong>Please switch your phones off or onto silent whilst playing your match to avoid disruption to you and your opponents.</strong></p>
<p>Please seek approval from your opponents if you need to have your phone on in special circumstances.</p>
<p><span style="white-space: pre;"> </span></p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Pool Players</span></strong></p>
<p><strong>The TWL committee are continuing to take names for pool players and the waiting list and will be happy to add them on this season.</strong></p>
<p>If at any time you need to use a pool player, then you must contact your division representative, who will approve a pool player for you, from the list.  However if no pool players are available then the committee will agree a pool player with you.</p>
<p><strong>Do not </strong>assume that you can get your own replacement and continue without the approval of the committee. If this occurs then your match will be void and full points will be awarded to the opposition.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Re-arranged Matches</span></strong></p>
<p>All re-arranged matches must be played <strong>within 2 weeks</strong> of your scheduled match. If you know well in advance you are not able to play on scheduled date, bring the fixture forward rather than play on a later date.  This will prevent a big back log of fixtures later in the season.</p>
<p>If injury does not allow you to play within two weeks, then your partner must get a pool player, please consult your divisional representative and rearrange your court.</p>
<p>Rearranged matches can be played on the scheduled court on a different date as long as it has been agreed with the court owners.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Please note</span></strong></p>
<p>Please be aware that rearranged matches on public courts will incur a cost.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Fair Game policy</span></strong></p>
<p>1. The Tennis Widows League members must promote a fair game within matches played.  Bad sportsmanship identified as cheating, ill manners and poor conduct will not be tolerated, and will be acted upon accordingly.</p>
<p>1.1 Should [1] above be compromised by any of the named actions then the TWL will be forced to take action through the policy procedure as stated in [2].</p>
<p>2. Complaints about named fellow competitor/s must be in writing (email accepted) and received by a committee member with in 48 hrs of the so said incident.</p>
<p>2.1 The complaint as set out in [2] will be dealt with by the whole committee and all parties named as involved will be contacted.  On consultation by the committee a disciplinary actions may be taken where necessary.</p>
<p>3. Disciplinary actions will range from “one warning” to “exclusion from the league”</p>
